{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "hexagonal-restaurant",
    "description": "End-to-end API checks for the monolith `configuration` app (table + order + kitchen in one JVM).\n\n## Akış (Happy path)\n1. **`Place order` önce** — masa seed ile **AVAILABLE** olmalı; **OCCUPIED** iken `place order` **400** döner (domain kuralı).\n2. **`order.order.placed`** → mutfak `RECEIVED` kaydı; table consumer masayı **OCCUPIED** yapar.\n3. Kafka gecikmesi: `GET .../tables/{id}` hâlâ **AVAILABLE** ise birkaç saniye bekleyip tekrarlayın.\n\n## Before you run\n1. **Start**: Kafka + Postgres, then `ConfigurationApplication` from the `configuration` module.\n2. **Kafka**: `spring.kafka.listener.auto-startup: true` (varsayılan). Broker: profile **`kafka`** + `application-kafka.yml` veya `SPRING_KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS`.\n3. **`orderId`**: adım 1 **Tests** ile environment’a yazılır. **`kitchenOrderId`**: adım **4** (`GET .../by-order/...`); **404** ise consumer bekleyin.\n4. **Seeded data** (`DataSeeder`): `tableId` = `aaaaaaaa-0000-0000-0000-000000000001`, burger `menuItemId` = `bbbbbbbb-0000-0000-0000-000000000001`.\n5. **Kapatma**: `POST .../close` → masa **AVAILABLE** (yeniden place order için).\n\n## Topics (reference)\n- `order.order.placed` → kitchen `RECEIVED`; table **OCCUPIED**\n- `kitchen.order.ready` → order **READY**\n- `table.order.delivered` → order **DELIVERED**",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Happy path – full flow",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Place order",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.environment.set('orderId', j.orderId);",
                  "pm.test('Order PENDING in body', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('PENDING');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tableId\": \"{{tableId}}\",\n  \"orderItems\": [\n    {\n      \"menuItemId\": \"{{menuItemId}}\",\n      \"quantity\": 1\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/orders",
            "description": "Masa yalnızca **AVAILABLE** iken sipariş kabul edilir (**OCCUPIED** → 400). **201** → `order.order.placed` (mutfak + masa consumer)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Get table (expect OCCUPIED after Kafka)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Table OCCUPIED (retry if still AVAILABLE — Kafka)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('OCCUPIED');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/tables/{{tableId}}",
            "description": "`OrderPlaced` sonrası table consumer masayı **OCCUPIED** yapar. Hâlâ **AVAILABLE** ise birkaç saniye bekleyip bu isteği tekrarlayın."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Get order (expect PENDING)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Order PENDING', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('PENDING');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}",
            "description": "`orderId` adım **1**’deki **Tests** script’i ile environment’a yazılır."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Get kitchen order by order id",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.environment.set('kitchenOrderId', j.kitchenOrderId);",
                  "pm.test('Kitchen RECEIVED', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('RECEIVED');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/kitchen/orders/by-order/{{orderId}}",
            "description": "Kafka `OrderPlaced` consumer mutfak kaydını oluşturduktan sonra **kitchenOrderId** döner. **404** ise consumer henüz işlememiş veya Kafka kapalıdır; birkaç saniye bekleyip tekrar deneyin."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "5. Kitchen – start preparing",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Kitchen PREPARING', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('PREPARING');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/kitchen/orders/{{kitchenOrderId}}/start",
            "description": "`kitchenOrderId` adım **4** ile environment’a yazılır (veya `GET /api/kitchen/orders/{id}`)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "6. Kitchen – mark ready",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Kitchen READY', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('READY');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/kitchen/orders/{{kitchenOrderId}}/ready",
            "description": "→ **PREPARING** sonrası **READY**, `kitchen.order.ready` yayınlanır."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "7. Get order (expect READY after Kafka)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Order READY (async)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('READY');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}",
            "description": "Kafka consumer işledikten sonra sipariş **READY** olmalı."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "8. Table – mark order delivered",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Delivered payload', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.orderId).to.eql(pm.environment.get('orderId'));",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"orderId\": \"{{orderId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/tables/{{tableId}}/deliver",
            "description": "`table.order.delivered` yayınlanır."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "9. Get order (expect DELIVERED after Kafka)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Order DELIVERED (async)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('DELIVERED');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "10. Close table",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Table AVAILABLE', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('AVAILABLE');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/tables/{{tableId}}/close",
            "description": "Masa tekrar **AVAILABLE** olur."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "11. Get table (expect AVAILABLE)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Table AVAILABLE', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('AVAILABLE');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/tables/{{tableId}}"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Sırayı bozmadan çalıştırın. **1** `Place order` (masa **AVAILABLE**). **2** masanın **OCCUPIED** olması Kafka’ya bağlı — gerekirse tekrarlayın. **`orderId`** adım 1’de; **`kitchenOrderId`** adım **4**’te set edilir (**404** ise consumer bekleyin)."
    },
    {
      "name": "Helpers",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get order (no status assert)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}",
            "description": "Ham JSON görmek için."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get table (no status assert)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/tables/{{tableId}}"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Open table (staff — makes OCCUPIED)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/tables/{{tableId}}/open",
            "description": "Masayı **OCCUPIED** yapar. Happy path’te **kullanmayın**: sonrasında `place order` yalnızca **AVAILABLE** kabul ettiği için **400** alırsınız. Kapatıp (`close`) tekrar **AVAILABLE** yapın veya yeni seed tablo kullanın."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get kitchen order by order id",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/kitchen/orders/by-order/{{orderId}}",
            "description": "404 = henüz mutfak kaydı yok (Kafka consumer bekleniyor)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get kitchen order by kitchen id",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/kitchen/orders/{{kitchenOrderId}}",
            "description": "Mutfak aggregate PK ile detay."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
